reviews.review:
It was better than TLJ... That's all I needed.
JJ did what he could after what RJ did in ep 8.

If you hated the horrible abomination that was last Jedi. This movie came across as a public apology to Star wars fans.  It was so good that it actually made me like the prior to movies more.  The first 10 minutes was a fast forwarded version of what the previous movie was supposed to be.  The remainder was filled with carful story crafted to undo the damage done by it's predecessor.  It felt and looked like a star wars film should. It made me actually care about the characters. Something that neither force awakens or last Jedi was able to do.  Abrams reigned in and clearly knew what he should and shouldn't do in a star wars movie.
CRYING!!!!  This can’t be the end!!
The Star Wars movies have gotten worse and worse. Save your money.
IT is THE END worth seeing  on the big screen

Fantastic visuals, amazing sound effects, epic soundtrack. That's it that's all it had. There was no laughter, there was nothing so you could deem legendary, they didn't even bother to answer questions from previous movies.
the writers and directors of this movie had absolutely no idea how the force works the introduced concepts we've never heard of and they failed in their execution of what should have been the greatest finale of any series ever.
Such a good final episode. Best of the recent trilogy and so many satisfying beats. If you are a Star Wars fan you should be happy with this send off.

Great family fun! Is it on par with the original trilogy? Absolutely not!! But hey, it’s hard to duplicate greatness!! Bottom line, my kids loved it and I got to share the experience with them. I watched the original Star Wars with my father in 1977 and that memory will always be cherished!! Thank you George Lucas and Disney for another great memory!

Visually entertaining and extremely shallow, would best describe Disney's third run at Star Wars. Fan or not, the film does very little, structurally, to paint a story with any lasting sense of tangibility. It's hard to feel closer to any of the characters after watching Rise of Skywalker. Instead of developing lesser characters in the series, we are once again introduced to more. Where there were attempts at development, they were cut short and quickly rushed into the next series of explosions. There's no real sense of accomplishment with this film. Abrams may have succeeded in completing this film series, but he and Disney failed to create any sense of closure.

Ending the Skywalker saga, hard to express how I feel about this messy movie. Every Star Wars fan should watch and see the epic conclusion. Fan base will be divided but its impossible to live up to Star Wars expectations
